line_1: His soul was shook, and every nerve was thrill'd;
line_2: Bleeding and pale he gaz'd, with horror fill'd,

line_1: Which when I saw, my heart with pleasure thrill'd,
line_2: For there sweet Damon oft my eyes beheld.

line_1: As he who now with 'sdainful fury thrill'd
line_2: Low lays the house which that of cards doth build,

line_1: As he who now with 'sdainful fury thrill'd
line_2: And many an Epick to his rage shall yield;

line_1: As he who now with 'sdainful fury thrill'd
line_2: And many a poet quit th' Aonian field;

line_1: A conscious Horror through his Bosom thrill'd:
line_2: Pale stood the Brother — to a Statue chill'd,

line_1: Goads each fine nerve, with new sensation thrill'd,
line_2: Bends the reluctant limbs with power unwill'd;
